   "source": [
    "# Tutorial with Pennylane\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates several examples of generating Quantum Convolutional Neural Networks (QCNNs) using the package. Default circuits/ansatzes for convolution and pooling operations are shown, such as the CRZ gate for convolutions and CNOT for pooling, to facilitate an easy visual representation of the package's functionality. The section [custom unitaries](#sec_customunitary) illustrates how to specify custom unitaries for convolutions, pooling, or other primitives."
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1669c9a9-9853-49f3-86ca-765242d0670c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "___\n",

    "# Load libraries\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Core library functionality\n",
    "from hierarqcal import Qcnn, Qfree, Qconv, Qpool, Qdense, plot_motif, plot_motifs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "034cc07e-04b7-40ce-9ab5-6a414cdaf5c4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Specific to Pennylane\n",
    "import pennylane as qml\n",
    "from hierarqcal.pennylane import get_param_info_pennylane, execute_circuit_pennylane\n",
    "\n",
    "# Specify QNode\n",
    "dev = qml.device(\"default.qubit\", wires=[i + 1 for i in range(8)])\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "@qml.qnode(dev)\n",
    "def circuit(motif, params):\n",
    "    response_wire = motif.head.Q_avail[-1]  # This is the 'last' available qubit\n",
    "    execute_circuit_pennylane(motif, params)  # This executes the compute graph in order\n",
    "    return qml.expval(qml.PauliZ(response_wire))\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Specify drawer\n",
    "qml.drawer.use_style(\"black_white\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6b04931a-bb24-45f1-a279-7d321d0edfd0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Basic example\n",
    "We create one of the architectures discussed in [Lourens et al.](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2210.15073.pdf). This architecture is semantically described as repeating a convolution of stride 1 and pooling from bottom to top on 8 qubits until one remain.\n",
    "\n",
    "<img src=\"../img/hierarchical_motifs.drawio.svg\" alt=\"hierarchical motifs\" width=\"900\"/>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "8a2b1b8e-b7c9-45d5-969c-bd8d5f7efa59",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 2100x900 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Build circuit\n",
    "motif = Qfree(8) + (Qconv(1) + Qpool(filter=\"right\")) * 3\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get param info\n",
    "total_coef_count, coef_indices = get_param_info_pennylane(motif)\n",
    "params = np.random.uniform(0, np.pi, total_coef_count)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Draw\n",
    "fig, ax = qml.draw_mpl(circuit)(motif, params)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "f08396be-d039-46b8-bc32-0c8056a5da5e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Number of coefficients:3\n",
      "Coefficients per layer:\n",
      "{0: range(0, 1), 1: None, 2: range(1, 2), 3: None, 4: range(2, 3), 5: None}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(f\"Number of coefficients:{total_coef_count}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Coefficients per layer:\\n{coef_indices}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "accd6b0d-8f21-49e5-a227-525ebca229aa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "1.0\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Execute the circuit\n",
    "print(circuit(motif, params))"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "14520029-eebf-438e-be9c-53effe3d27a5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Building blocks\n",
    "Circuit architectures are created by stacking motifs hierarchacially, the lowest level motifs (primitives) are building blocks for higher level ones. On a high level you can regard a primitive as a layer such as convolution or pooling and we're creating a sequence of layers for the circuit. This view only captures hierarchical architectures of two levels (*level 1 -> primitives, level 2 -> sequence of primitves*). The framework is more general in that there is no limit to the number of levels used to represent an architecture. See the comparison below:\n",
    "\n",
    "**Layer view**\n",
    " - qcnn = (Convolution, Pooling, Convolution, Pooling, Convolution, Convolution, Convolution, Pooling, Convolution, Pooling)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Hierarchical view**\n",
    " - m2_1 = (Convolution, Pooling)\n",
    " - m2_2 = (Convolution, Convolution)\n",
    " - m3_1 = (m2_1, m2_1)\n",
    " - qcnn = (m3_1, m2_2, m3_1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a5b6576b-6d20-49dd-a4c2-3eb7afd15091",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Free qubit primitive\n",
    "We first need to specify the qubits for operations to act, this is achieved with the `Qfree` primitive. It is a special motif with no operational effect that makes qubits available and unavailable for succesive operations. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "070b4ef2-39d4-4cb1-83c0-d83e01f0f07c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Free primitive, can also recieve a list of qubit lables to make available.\n",
    "free = Qfree(10)  # or Qfree([2,6,4,10]) or Qfree([\"q1\", \"q2\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plot_motif(free)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9736cb8d-425e-4de7-b094-9afa2b08964e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

    "To visualise the convolution operation we free up 8 qubits and add a convolution of stride 5 motif"

    "# Convolution of stride 3, try out other stride values\n",
    "convolution = Qconv(stride=5)\n",
    "conv_on_8_qubits = Qfree(8) + convolution\n",
    "\n",
    "# Note the type of 'conv_on_8_qubits', it's a qcnn with two motifs: (Qfree, Qconv)\n",
    "print(f\"Type of object\\t {type(conv_on_8_qubits)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"First motif\\t {type(conv_on_8_qubits.tail)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Second motif\\t {type(conv_on_8_qubits.tail.next)}\")\n",
    "plot_motifs(conv_on_8_qubits, all_motifs=True)"

    "## Reverse binary tree"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "0b78d2c5-853f-448b-aacb-34b9073ba890",

       "\"></div><div class=\"floating-box\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\n",
       "\"></div><div class=\"floating-box\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\n",
       "\"></div><div class=\"floating-box\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\n",
       "\"></div><div class=\"floating-box\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\n",
       "\"></div>"

       "<IPython.core.display.HTML object>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "### Reverse binary tree\n",
    "\n",
    "# Change these values\n",
    "# ---------\n",
    "N = 8  # any power of two\n",
    "s_c = 1  # 1,2,3, ...\n",
    "f = \"inside\"  # right, left, inside, outside, even, odd\n",
    "s_p = 0  # 0,1,2,3, ...\n",
    "# ---------\n",
    "\n",
    "# level 1\n",
    "m1_1 = Qconv(stride=s_c)\n",
    "m1_2 = Qpool(stride=s_p, filter=f)\n",
    "# level 2\n",
    "m2_1 = m1_1 + m1_2\n",
    "# level 3\n",
    "m3_1 = Qfree(N) + m2_1 * int(np.log2(N))\n",
    "\n",
    "figs = plot_motifs(m3_1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "c408b418-3feb-42ba-be53-4d3f50a20b5d",

    "\n",
    "# Draw\n",
    "fig, ax = qml.draw_mpl(circuit)(m3_1, params)"
   ]

    "## More arbitrary examples to show what is possible"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "cc563ad9-b1f1-49a0-ba6c-2a1b198d4035",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 5100x900 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "m1 = Qfree(6) + Qconv()\n",
    "m2 = m1 + Qpool(1, \"000101\")\n",
    "m3 = m2 + Qfree(8) + Qconv(1) + Qpool(2, \"11111110\")\n",
    "m4 = m3 + Qfree(4) + (Qconv(1) + Qpool(0, \"even\")) * 2\n",
    "m5 = m4 + m4\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get param info\n",
    "total_coef_count, coef_indices = get_param_info_pennylane(m5)\n",
    "params = np.random.uniform(0, np.pi, total_coef_count)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Draw\n",
    "fig, ax = qml.draw_mpl(circuit)(m5, params)"
   ]
  },

    "figs = plot_motifs(\n",
    "    m5, all_motifs=True, figsize=(2.5, 2.5), node_large=150, node_small=50, edge_width=1\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "ec0349e1-d4cb-4765-b8ca-17e71ceed978",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 15100x900 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "N = 8\n",
    "# level 1\n",
    "m1_1 = Qconv(2)\n",
    "m1_2 = Qpool(filter=\"left\")\n",
    "# level 2\n",
    "m2_1 = m1_1 + m1_2\n",
    "# level 3\n",
    "m3_1 = Qfree(N) + m2_1 * int(np.log2(N))\n",
    "final_motif = (m3_1 + Qfree([1, 3, 5]) + Qconv(5) + m3_1) * 4\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get param info\n",
    "total_coef_count, coef_indices = get_param_info_pennylane(final_motif)\n",
    "params = np.random.uniform(0, np.pi, total_coef_count)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Draw\n",
    "fig, ax = qml.draw_mpl(circuit)(final_motif, params)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fd865c61-a965-4a02-9645-3f58841a8341",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Multiscale Entanglement Renormalization Ansatz (MERA)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "id": "e7d55491-29fd-490c-9f43-719cd0a6d207",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1300x900 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "### MERA like\n",
    "N = 8\n",
    "# level 1\n",
    "m1_1 = Qconv(1, 2)\n",
    "m1_2 = Qconv(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "m1_3 = Qpool(filter=\"1001\")\n",
    "m1_4 = Qpool(2, filter=\"001001\")\n",
    "m1_5 = Qpool(filter=\"outside\")\n",
    "# level 2\n",
    "m2_1 = m1_2 + m1_1\n",
    "m2_2 = m1_3 + m1_4\n",
    "m2_3 = m1_5\n",
    "# level 3\n",
    "m3_1 = Qfree(N) + (m2_1 + m2_2) * 2 + m2_1\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get param info\n",
    "total_coef_count, coef_indices = get_param_info_pennylane(m3_1)\n",
    "params = np.random.uniform(0, np.pi, total_coef_count)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Draw\n",
    "fig, ax = qml.draw_mpl(circuit)(m3_1, params)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bb88b1e8-1eeb-445e-9d17-cd1cfc5b59e7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Random QCNNs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "id": "1de73952-5198-4784-8c0c-34b44209569f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1600x900 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# More structure\n",
    "import random\n",
    "import operator\n",
    "from functools import reduce\n",
    "from hierarqcal import Qmotifs\n",
    "\n",
    "N = 8\n",
    "M = Qcnn(N)\n",
    "n = len(M.tail.Q_avail)\n",
    "while n > 1:\n",
    "    p = [\n",
    "        Qpool(s_p, filter=i_filter)\n",
    "        for i_filter in (\"right\", \"left\", \"even\", \"odd\", \"inside\", \"outside\")\n",
    "        for s_p in range(n)\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    c = [\n",
    "        Qconv(stride=s_c, step=s_t, offset=s_o)\n",
    "        for s_c in range(1, n, 1)\n",
    "        for s_t in range(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "        for s_o in range(n)\n",
    "    ]  # + [Qdense()]\n",
    "    M = M + random.choice(c) + random.choice(p)\n",
    "    n = len(M.head.Q_avail)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get param info\n",
    "total_coef_count, coef_indices = get_param_info_pennylane(M)\n",
    "params = np.random.uniform(0, np.pi, total_coef_count)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Draw\n",
    "fig, ax = qml.draw_mpl(circuit)(M, params)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "id": "05e3ba8c-5f7c-462c-9990-41b50f4ced68",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1300x900 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# loose\n",
    "import random\n",
    "import operator\n",
    "from functools import reduce\n",
    "from hierarqcal import Qmotifs\n",
    "\n",
    "N = 8\n",
    "M = Qcnn(N)\n",
    "n = len(M.tail.Q_avail)\n",
    "while n > 1:\n",
    "    p = [\n",
    "        Qpool(s_p, filter=i_filter)\n",
    "        for i_filter in (\"right\", \"left\", \"even\", \"odd\", \"inside\", \"outside\")\n",
    "        for s_p in range(n)\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    c = [\n",
    "        Qconv(stride=s_c, step=s_t, offset=s_o)\n",
    "        for s_c in range(1, n, 1)\n",
    "        for s_t in range(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "        for s_o in range(n)\n",
    "    ] + [Qdense()]\n",
    "    M = M + random.choice(c) + random.choice(p)\n",
    "    n = len(M.head.Q_avail)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get param info\n",
    "total_coef_count, coef_indices = get_param_info_pennylane(M)\n",
    "params = np.random.uniform(0, np.pi, total_coef_count)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Draw\n",
    "fig, ax = qml.draw_mpl(circuit)(M, params)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bede20f2-cee9-47a1-ad28-6a7fca604625",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Specifying unitaries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "id": "5a2332df-b595-43be-b5a6-b1c57c466d09",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Pooling circuit\n",
    "def V(bits, symbols=None):\n",
    "    qml.CRZ(symbols[0], wires=[bits[0], bits[1]])\n",
    "    qml.PauliX(wires=bits[0])\n",
    "    qml.CRX(symbols[1], wires=[bits[0], bits[1]])\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convolution circuit\n",
    "def U(bits, symbols=None):\n",
    "    qml.RZ(symbols[0], wires=bits[1])\n",
    "    qml.CNOT(wires=[bits[1], bits[0]])\n",
    "    qml.RZ(symbols[1], wires=bits[0])\n",
    "    qml.RY(symbols[2], wires=bits[1])\n",
    "    qml.CNOT(wires=[bits[0], bits[1]])\n",
    "    qml.RY(symbols[3], wires=bits[1])\n",
    "    qml.CNOT(wires=[bits[1], bits[0]])\n",
    "    qml.RZ(symbols[4], wires=bits[0])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bd6ea430-99d2-4b8e-97bd-3c0621aa9388",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Convolution**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "952895a5-a724-43e0-a245-7939cb009dcb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x300 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "convolution_ansatz = Qfree(2) + Qconv(convolution_mapping=(U, 5))\n",
    "# Get param info\n",
    "total_coef_count, coef_indices = get_param_info_pennylane(convolution_ansatz)\n",
    "params = np.random.uniform(0, np.pi, total_coef_count)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Draw\n",
    "fig, ax = qml.draw_mpl(circuit)(convolution_ansatz, params)"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   ]

   "execution_count": 25,
   "id": "c7a98534-f932-4cdf-95ae-695e1ab9dca6",

   "source": [
    "m = (\n",
    "    Qfree(8)\n",
    "    + (\n",
    "        Qconv(1, convolution_mapping=(U, 5))\n",
    "        + Qpool(filter=\"left\", pooling_mapping=(V, 4))\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    * 3\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get param info\n",
    "total_coef_count, coef_indices = get_param_info_pennylane(m)\n",
    "params = np.random.uniform(0, np.pi, total_coef_count)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Draw\n",
    "fig, ax = qml.draw_mpl(circuit)(m, params)"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "36f659c8-5857-4b44-bfbf-18378b89ac6c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Cycle through unitary ansatzes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "f387216f-df07-45c7-b32e-c5df465fffde",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Pooling circuit\n",
    "def V_1(bits, symbols=None):  # 1\n",
    "    qml.CRX(symbols[0], wires=[bits[0], bits[1]])\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def V_2(bits, symbols=None):  # 0\n",
    "    qml.CNOT(wires=[bits[0], bits[1]])\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convolution circuit\n",
    "def U_1(bits, symbols=None):  # 1\n",
    "    qml.CRZ(symbols[0], wires=[bits[0], bits[1]])\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def U_2(bits, symbols=None):  # 1\n",
    "    qml.CRY(symbols[0], wires=[bits[0], bits[1]])\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "function_mappings = {\n",
    "    \"convolution\": [(U_1, 1), (U_2, 1)],\n",
    "    \"pooling\": [(V_1, 1), (V_2, 0)],\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "id": "b14455f0-7b64-4b9f-a35b-314832982e95",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 4300x1700 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "qcnn = Qcnn(16, function_mappings=function_mappings)\n",
    "\n",
    "qcnn = qcnn + (Qconv(2) + Qpool(1, \"outside\")) * 4\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get param info\n",
    "total_coef_count, coef_indices = get_param_info_pennylane(qcnn)\n",
    "params = np.random.uniform(0, np.pi, total_coef_count)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Draw\n",
    "fig, ax = qml.draw_mpl(circuit)(qcnn, params)"
   ]
  },
